com.bluegosling.collections.immutable

Class HamtPersistentMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • com.bluegosling.collections.immutable.AbstractImmutableMap<K,V>
        • com.bluegosling.collections.immutable.HamtPersistentMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys in the map
    V - the type of value in the map
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    PersistentMap<K,V>, Map<K,V>

    public class HamtPersistentMap<K,V>
extends AbstractImmutableMap<K,V>
implements PersistentMap<K,V>
    An implementation of PersistentMap that uses an immutable hash array-mapped trie (HAMT) plus path copying on updates. This is an immutable and persistent version of HamtMap.

    Each level of the trie contains information for 4 bits of the hash code and thus can have up to 16 children. This means the trie can have a depth of up to eight.

    See Also:
    HamtMap
